 "Type the learning objectives for this resource.": "Zadajte vzdel\u00e1vacie ciele pre tento zdroj.", 
 "Teachers should keep the following in mind when using this iDevice: <ol><li>Think about the number of different types of activity planned for your resource that will be visually signalled in the content. Avoid using too many different types or classification of activities otherwise learner may become confused. Usually three or four different types are more than adequate for a teaching resource.<\/li><li>From a visual design perspective, avoid having two iDevices immediately following each other without any text in between. If this is required, rather collapse two questions or events into one iDevice. <\/li><li>Think about activities where the perceived benefit of doing the activity outweighs the time and effort it will take to complete the activity. <\/li><\/ol>": "U\u010ditelia by pri pou\u017eit\u00ed tohoto iDevice mali bra\u0165 do \u00favahy: <ol><li> Prem\u00fd\u0161\u013eajte nad mno\u017estvom r\u00f4znych zam\u00fd\u0161\u013ean\u00fdch aktiv\u00edt, ktor\u00e9 bud\u00fa v obsahu vizu\u00e1lne ozna\u010den\u00e9. Vyhnite sa pr\u00edli\u0161 ve\u013ek\u00e9mu mno\u017estvu r\u00f4znych typov \u010di klasifik\u00e1ci\u00ed aktiv\u00edt, preto\u017ee to m\u00f4\u017ee vies\u0165 k zm\u00e4teniu \u0161tudentov. Obvykle sta\u010dia tri a\u017e \u0161tyri r\u00f4zne typy na jednu v\u00fdukov\u00fa jednotku.<\/li><li> Pre preh\u013eadnos\u0165 sa v\u017edy sna\u017ete vklada\u0165 medzi dve iDevice text. Pokia\u013e to ale nejde, rad\u0161ej zhrnite dve ot\u00e1zky \u010di pr\u00edpady do jedn\u00e9ho iDevice.<\/li><li> Berte do \u00favahy aktivity, u ktor\u00fdch predpokladan\u00fd efekt preva\u017euje nad \u010dasom a \u00fasil\u00edm, ktor\u00e9 s\u00fa nutn\u00e9 na ich dokon\u010denie.<\/li><\/ol>", 
